<2ND_LINE>AM-Denmark-Robbery,0234</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Policeman Killed in Big Postal Robbery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 22-year-old policeman died late
Thursday night after bandits, two of them disguised as police, shot
him in the head with a sawed-off shotgun during Denmark's biggest
postal robbery, Danish radio said.
   The robbers fled early Thursday with booty of nearly $1.5 million
_ $1.3 million in Danish and foreign currency and $190,000 in bonds,
the report said.
   The holdup took place at the central post office as postal
workers were unloading a truck which had just returned from picking
up deposits from post offices, where many Danes pay their bills.
   The four robbers were allowed on the premises after two of them
dressed as police flashed what appeared to be badges. They knocked
down one of the guards in the truck and loaded 30 sacks full of
money into an orange van.
   A police patrol chanced by and tried to stop the holdup. One
officer was blasted at close range before the robbers sped off in
the van. The second patrolman fired at the van as it sped away,
shattering its rear window.
   The van was later found abandoned in a city garage.
   Police said they had few clues.
   Police and passers-by gathered at the shooting site after the
death of the young policeman was announced, leaving flower wreaths
and lighting candles.
</TEXT>
