<TEXT>
   Auto mechanic Ben DeRosier and his wife sat
in the lobby of The Sharper Image's corporate office, waiting to
convince a product buyer that their electric fingernail file is a
retailer's dream come true.
   ``I work in an office where all the girls are into long nails ...
and after using this the nails are so smooth you can run them down
your stockings without causing even the tiniest snag, something I'd
never do after the beauty parlor,'' said Doris DeRosier.
   The couple from Fairfield were among the small crowd of inventors
who every month, gizmos in hand, get their foot in the door of the
high-tech gadget purveyor in hopes of getting their devices into the
company's mail-order catalog and stores.
   In search of unique merchandise, The Sharper Image for two years
has held open house on the first Wednesday of every month. About 35
inventors a month from across the country attend, including some
manufacturers offering exclusive rights to their products.
