<TEXT>
   In a turnabout of the usual coattails
scenario, Republicans hoped a strong showing by Sen. John Heinz
would carry George Bush to victory in Pennsylvania's close
presidential race.
   An Oct. 28-30 poll by the Pittsburgh Post-Gazette and the
Philadelphia Daily News showed Heinz favored for a third term by 75
percent of the 618 registered and likely voters surveyed. Democrat
Joseph Vignola, former Philadelphia city controller, had 18 percent,
with 5 percent undecided.
