Michael Dukakis with 46 percent and 5 percent undecided in the
battle for Pennsylvania's 25 electoral votes.
   Bush's attack on Dukakis' positions on gun control and abortion
appeared to have helped the vice president in rural central
Pennsylvania, as well as in the traditionally Democratic northeast
region. Heinz has been campaigning across the state, focusing on
Bush's election rather than his own.
