<TEXT>
   Charles S. Robb, a former governor and
son-in-law of President Lyndon Johnson, looked for a landslide
victory over a longshot GOP opponent Tuesday to become Virginia's
first Democrat elected to the Senate since 1966.
   But the strength of Robb, who led by as much as 50 percentage
