<HEAD>Bush, Sen. Wallop, Rep. Cheney Poised for GOP Sweep</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHEYENNE, Wyo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republicans appeared poised for a sweep of
top races on the Wyoming ballot Tuesday, with Sen. Malcolm Wallop
and Rep. Dick Cheney favored to win re-election and Vice President
George Bush expected to capture the state's three electoral votes.
   Wallop used a war chest of $1.2 million in his bid for a third
