<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street 10am,0244</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was higher early today at the
start of what is expected to be another quiet session.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 7.64 points at
2,164.47 after a half-hour of trading at 10 a.m. EST.
   Advancing issues edged out declining ones by around 5 to 3 on the
New York Stock Exchange, with 549 issues up, 352 down and 508
unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 22.86 million shares.
   Through most of this week, trading has been dampened by the
market's anticipation of upcoming events: notably Friday's release
of U.S. unemployment data for October and the presidential election
next Tuesday.
   Stocks have come under some pressure from the dollar's persistent
decline in recent days, which has raised fears that the Federal
Reserve could bolster the U.S. currency by nudging interest rates
higher.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks had
edged up 0.24 to 157.24.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index was up
0.09 at 299.92.
   On Wednesday, the Dow Jones industrial average rose 5.87 points
to 2,156.83.
   Declining issues edged out advances by around 4 to 3 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 842 issues down, 598 up and 543 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 161.30 million shares, up from 151.25
million in Tuesday's session.
</TEXT>
