<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Only version planned.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
251,307 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
250,502, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 233,401 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 165,505 cars this week,
compared with 162,323 a week ago and 158,044 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 85,802,
compared with last week's 88,179 and last year's 75,357.
   Canadian automakers were to build 21,071 cars this week, down
from 22,463 a week ago and down from last year's 22,521.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,720, compared
with 21,841 a week ago and 18,295 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
